<p align="center"><strong><font size="+1">Lassa Victim Recovers</font></strong> 
<p>LAGOS, Nigeria, June 28 (Agence France-Presse)--A West German doctor who was sent home to Hamburg in March with a little-known and often fatal African disease has recovered and returned to work in Nigeria, it was announced today.&nbsp; Dr. Bernhard Mandrella, who works at a hospital in Onitsha Province ha[d] contracted Lassa fever.</p>
